  "text": "The amino acids comprising the L-domain region within the parental M51R virus and recombinant M40 are shown in Figure 1 . In contrast to the single PPPY L-domain motif within the M protein of M51R, the M40 recombinant was engineered to possess both the PTAP and overlapping PPEY motif from the VP40 protein of Ebola virus. The presence of the PTAP motif enables the M40 virus to recruit host protein Tsg101, which contributes to efficient budding of this recombinant virus. [CITATION_1] Thus, it was of interest to determine whether the presence of the PTAP motif and the Ebola sequences in general provided any replication advantage or modification of pathogenesis for the M40 recombinant in a mouse model of infection, compared to that of control virus M51R Fig. 1 .",
